Home - Ankyra Therapeutics Team Contact Select Page Ankyra is developing cancer therapies based on localized cytokines that prime a systemic adaptive immune Ankyra is developing a platform to significantly improve both the safety and efficacy of cytokine immunotherapies for Systemic dosing of these powerful immune stimulants has historically been limited by broad immune activation and We have developed methods to localize cytokines specifically and persistently within tumors thereby creating intense hot spots of inflammation that activate a comprehensive immune Our mission is to translate this approach into the clinic and demonstrate superior efficacy compared to available Management Team Tillman Gerngross, President and Dane Wittrup, Darrell Irvine, Michael Schmidt, Chief Scientific Officer Gregory , EVP of Process and Manufacturing Sciences Board of Directors Tillman Gerngross, & CEO of Adagio and Adimab, LLC Terry McGuire Partner, Polaris Partners Ajay Royan Partner, Mithril Capital Newbury Street • Floor Boston, MA

Holy Grail HOLY GRAIL WHY JOIN CONTACT BAYES WHY JOIN CONTACT Planet Earth in In Humanity faced multiple challenges, breakthroughs in energy storage and production, CO2 capture and storage, catalysis, and new materials to enable a zero waste economy were needed Humans did an amazing job creating multiple scientific breakthroughs but super humans or new research methods were needed to tackle the scale of the environmental challenges being faced THE WORLD WE WANT TO HELP BUILD autonomous R&D In R&D is autonomous Research, Development and Engineering are merged, humans now have full control of materials from atoms to working devices STORAGE In several energy storage breakthroughs were needed to enable full use of renewable From cheaper grid storage to more energy dense batteries to enable electric airplanes ENERGY Fossil fuels outcompeted In energy storage systems are carbon negative New battery chemistries and fuel cells that outperform fossil fuels were created, liquid and gas fuels are still being used but all storage systems are carbon negative due to advances in catalysis PRODUCTION In circa % of energy was still being produced with coal and gas, although natural gas power plants emit % less CO₂ than coal, new ways to produce energy were A large amount of resources were being allocated to fusion research but it was still not Solar and wind were advancing but energy storage became the bottleneck ENERGY MAKE FUSION NOT WAR In all electricity comes from renewable sources Advancements in super conductors and autonomous plasma research enabled net positive fusion, new low cost chemistries for grid storage enabled large solar and wind projects CARBON CAPTURE In million tons of CO₂ were being emitted every Carbon credits varied from $-100$ tonne but the cost of capture was around $ tonne directly from air and $ tonne at source with high energy expenditure and CAPEX caused by expensive With contemporary technology it was extremely challenging to make CO₂ capture economically viable and compete with CO₂ sources coming from Natural Gas A breakthrough in capture systems was needed to make direct capture less expensive and transform CO₂ into high value Even with a improvement in capture technology Billion dollars would be needed every year to capture all the CO₂ emitted yearly in CARBON CO₂ becomes useful In the Planet Earth is Carbon Negative Advancements in Energy production and carbon capture reduction technology enabled the planet to become carbon negative CHEMICAL PRODUCTION In almost all raw materials for plastics and pharmaceuticals came from fossil carbon Advancements in catalysis were needed to find alternative and sustainable chemical routes CO₂ IS RESOURCE CO₂ becomes a FRIEND In all chemical feedstocks are created from renewable sources In , ethylene and propylene are still the biggest chemical products by mass, due to the production of plastics and New catalysts enabled a shift to renewable feedstock production CIRCULAR MATERIALS In around 8 million tonnes of plastic packaging ended up in the ocean every year killing animals and destroying natural New materials with programmed or degradation by demand were In plastics were either too durable or not durable enough and were usually discarded as waste with no associated value ZERO WASTE Zero Zero Waste Society Development of new materials, recycling and up cycling methods enabled decomposition by Materials research and behavior changes enabled clean oceans, 0% of materials end up in the sea REUSABLE ROCKETS In a space industry revival was After building reusable rocket boosters, Spacex sent the first astronauts to the International Space Station in a United States built spaceship, the first since with the Space In kerosene was still being burned in propulsion systems but methane engines were being NASA was still using solid rocket boosters with oil derived propellants and liquid % of hydrogen production came from fossil fuel sources SPACE EXPLORATION NO GUILT SPACE EXPLORATION In Humans are multiplanetary There is a permanent station in the moon and Mars, no oil derived fuels are used in space exploration, new materials enabled super low cost space exploration and full reusability in A planet in equilibrium In Humans coexist with nature with exponential technology progress and no negative impact Holy Grail Inc Mountain View Evergreen Theragnostics Completes $19 Million Series A Capital Raise - Evergreen Theragnostics Skip to content Our services About us Our team News Contact Menu Our services About us Our team News Contact Our services About us Our team News Contact News Evergreen Theragnostics Completes $19 Million Series A Capital Raise June , JERSEY CITY, NJ, June , – Evergreen Theragnostics, , a radiopharmaceutical Contract Development and Manufacturing Organization (CDMO), today announced that it has raised $19M in a Series A financing The investment was made by private investors in common shares of the The funds will primarily be used for construction of a radiopharmaceutical manufacturing facility in Springfield, New The facility will be designed to meet the needs of companies in North America producing radiopharmaceuticals, including theragnostics, from early clinical development through full scale Construction of the facility, which will be built to global Good Manufacturing Practice (GMP) standards, is set to begin in the third quarter of “We are very pleased to have completed this investment round with such a supportive group of shareholders, especially in the midst of unprecedented market volatility resulting from ,” said James Cook, Chief Executive Officer of “The combination of compliance with global GMP, top industry talent, and strategic facility location, with seamless access to some of the world’s largest air transportation hubs including Newark Liberty International Airport in New Jersey and John Kennedy International Airport in New York, positions Evergreen Theragnostics to become a premier radiopharmaceutical manufacturing and distribution ” About Evergreen Theragnostics, Evergreen Theragnostics was established in to be a leading radiopharmaceutical Contract Development and Manufacturing Organization (CDMO). With a global GMP facility opening in , Evergreen will provide highly reliable manufacturing services for therapeutic and centrally distributed diagnostic radiopharmaceuticals, from early development through The company was founded by a team that brings a strong track record in theragnostic radiopharmaceutical commercialization, manufacturing process development, and regulatory affairs For more information, please visit . We turned the kitchen in our apartment into a lab and started After what felt like a million recipe iterations and countless thoughts of giving up, one day we got it right… really right! The Urban Wood Economy describes the financial investment and value of the life cycle of a city tree—from its planting and maintenance to its Planting & Maintenance Cities invest millions of dollars to plant and maintain trees on streets and in Pruning & Maintenance City Officials and private companies removes millions of trees across the US every Across the US, trees fall every year, equivalent to tons and $600m in landfill Tress are expensive and Right now, we lose most of our investment to landfills, burn piles, and low value That is where the Reforestation Hub concept comes Wood to Trees Revenues from product sales drive new planting in and around cities w proper maintenance Reforestation Hubs increase nursery capacity of local, native trees w higher chance of survival Reforestation Hubs create local jobs and target planting in underserved communities lacking green space Waste to Wood Reforestation Hubs divert waste from landfills, saving cities millions Reforestation Hubs connect wood to local businesses to make memorable products from and for their community Reforestation Hubs help market & sell those goods to tell the story of local, urban wood Subscribe Sign up with your email address to receive news and First Name Last Name Email Address Sign Up Thank you! FAQs About Us Features FAQs Careers Blog Home About Us FAQs Careers Blog FAQs More information can be found at our help center . About PrizePool What is PrizePool? PrizePool is a new way of saving money where the more you save, the more chances you have of winning one of thousands of cash prizes worth up to $50,000 every Risk free, and completely One lucky winner will win our grand prize of $25,000, every You’ll never lose your All deposits are FDIC insured and there are no fees or You’re automatically entered into the monthly drawings just by saving It’s that What are the prizes? Every month, thousands of PrizePool users will win cash prizes from $2 and One lucky winner will win the Grand Prize of $25,000 – every month! How much does it cost? Nothing! We’re completely free! How much do I need to get started? Any amount! Even one dollar saved will earn you as many as tickets to enter in the prize drawings, and there are thousands of winners every You could even win the Grand Prize! Are you a bank? We’re not your deposits are held by our partner bank, Evolve Bank & Trust, Member FDIC, and are protected by security and are FDIC insured up to $250 Is my money secure? All bank deposits in the US are insured by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC) up to $250 What’s the FDIC? The Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation is a US Government agency providing deposit insurance (hence the name) for people using commercial It was created in order to provide consumer trust in the banking system and financial backup in case your bank Being FDIC insured is also a mark of a quality bank, since the FDIC only insures and trustworthy financial How does it work How many Prizes are you giving away? There are over 4,000 winners totaling $50,000 in cash prizes including a $25,000 Grand Our official rules include a full breakdown of all the Calculating your tickets Every $1 deposited with PrizePool gets you 1 ticket per For example, if you have $500 deposited with PrizePool from September to September , you will have ,000 tickets! All tickets accrued during the month will be entered into the monthly How often are the drawings? Drawings are held at the beginning of every How does PrizePool make money? Evolve Bank & Trust, Member FDIC, pays us a small % of the interest pooled on the overall deposit amount but currently, all of this amount is used for the monthly No, but really, how do you offer all these prizes? Where % interest on a single deposit in a traditional savings account wouldn’t get you very far, we work with our partner bank and pool together the deposit interest on all those That way, thousands of lucky winners have a chance of winning a amount of cash, while all users are saving money towards their financial What if I didn’t win this month? If you didn’t win, you’re still saving money! You never lose your And every dollar in PrizePool will accrue new tickets in the following And of course, if you want to increase your chances of winning, you could always deposit Either way, you’re saving towards your future and your money will never be How do Referrals work? When you invite your friends to use PrizePool, they get a referral code which they enter when they create an This way, we know they’re your referrals, and both you and your friend win % of any prizes they Best of all, this works for as long as you’re both using PrizePool! Here’s an example of how this works, taking you and your friend Sarah to illustrate: You refer Sarah to PrizePool and she wins that month’s $100 First of all, congratulations to Sarah, but also you both win an additional $10 each ($100 x % = $10). • Sarah wins $110: $100 for her saving prize + $10 for her referral prize • You won $10 for the month: % of Sarah’s $100 So, in this example, just by using the referral code, the $100 prize actually means we’re giving away $120! Here’s another example where two of your referrals won prizes, your friends Sarah and Sarah wins the $100 prize and John wins the $20 The breakdown would look like this: • Sarah wins $110: $100 for her savings prize + $10 for her referral prize • John wins $22: $20 for his savings prize + $2 for his referral prize • You win $12: $10 for referring Sarah and getting % of her $100 prize + $2 for referring John and getting % of his $20 So, in that example, just by using the referral codes, $120 in prizes actually means we’re giving away $144! You can see that the more friends you invite to use PrizePool, the more chances you have to win, and the more money we’re giving And this extra winning will happen for as long as you and your friends are using Terms of service Privacy policy Legal About Us FAQs Official Rules Careers 1 No risk - There are no fees or charges made by 2 Fees - There are no fees charged by 3 Initial Deposit Requirement - There is no minimum deposit FDIC Banking services provided by: Evolve Bank & Trust Member FDIC Contact   About us About Us Features FAQs Careers Blog Home About Us FAQs Careers Blog PrizeP

Tecton: The Data Platform for Machine Learning - Tecton Tecton: The Data Platform for Machine Learning - Tecton Tecton Home About Us Careers Blog Request Early Access Request Early Access Toggle navigation Home About Us Careers Blog Request Early Access Tecton: The Data Platform for Machine Learning Posted by Mike Del Balso on April , | Featured Share on facebook Share on twitter Share on linkedin Today, Jeremy Hermann, Kevin Stumpf and I are excited to introduce Tecton, the company we founded just over a year Tecton’s mission is to make it easy and safe to put machine learning into production to power smart product This means bringing the best practices of machine learning development to everyone, and enabling every team to build with the speed, trust, and power of the industry’s most capable applied ML Our founding team met at Uber, where we created Michelangelo , the internal platform for building, deploying, and managing ML systems in We worked with dozens of teams tackling hundreds of business problems with ML, from user experiences like ETA prediction to operational decisions like fraud Across these efforts, we kept seeing the same pattern: data science teams would build promising offline prototypes, but would end up taking months (or quarters) of with engineering to actually get things fully “operationalized” and launched in Michelangelo addressed these problems with its integrated feature store and model management The platform connected a collaborative development environment with production infrastructure, enabling a Cambrian explosion of ML at Uber, where thousands of models and feature pipelines now run in We’ve since heard from countless companies across a variety of verticals, and they all reference the same familiar pains with deploying Some tech companies have developed custom internal solutions after wrestling with these problems for For everyone else, powering customer experiences in production with ML is still an extremely complex, expensive, and often insurmountable Most of that complexity originates in the data layer for ML (feature engineering, sharing, serving, monitoring, and much more), an area underserved by today’s ML That’s why we’re building Tecton, to make operational ML achievable for every Tecton is an data platform specifically built for ML, expanding on the ideas behind Michelangelo’s feature It accelerates and standardizes the data workflows that support the development and deployment of ML The goal is to improve , increase ROI on ML efforts, and fundamentally change how ML is developed within data science Making machine learning operational Machine learning has definitively left the lab and is now transforming how we develop software and what that software can It’s starting to power new customer experiences across nearly every industry, from predicting the availability of hospital beds to matching players of similar skill in online For problems like recommendations, pricing, personalized search, fraud detection, and supply chain optimization, ML is bringing step function improvements that weren’t possible with traditional These examples represent operational uses of ML, which is new terrain for most software Many teams have experience with offline, analytical uses of ML, which enable human through answering questions, generating insights, and exploring In contrast, with what we’ve begun to call “operational ML,” the goal is to enable machine Operational ML drives systems that make automated decisions in the product to power the customer experience, at scale and in Operational ML systems need to be and fully These systems have production SLAs, and make predictions at low latency (<100ms) and high They need to be thoroughly vetted to be trusted to drive the customer They often require integration with multiple software components and collaboration across several development Operational ML use cases need decisions now, not in a report next Dynamic prices, risk decisions, smart responses, and personalized experiences need to be generated and delivered in These models don’t have the luxury of time to wait for complete or corrected If something goes wrong, there’s no time to investigate and debug, so additional business logic (edge case handling, graceful degradation, ) needs to be deployed with the Operational ML use cases are and affect the bottom The product use cases that require ML tend to be and directly tied to revenue or cost Performance issues have direct business The behavior of these models drive the behavior of your Problems here mean costly mistakes and embarrassing customer Operational ML represents uncharted territory for most Teams that haven’t historically been “machine learning teams” are now asked to deploy and manage ML in Teams that produce analytics or insights are now asked to integrate those insights in the product Teams that have historically defined system behavior with rules engines or other logic are asked to replace it with These changes are happen

Contact - SonALASense Get Updates For Patients Our Science GBM About Us Leadership Investors News & Resources Contact Contact Us Please provide your contact information below if you wish to receive updates on our progress General Inquiries Notice: JavaScript is required for this Press Inquiries Notice: JavaScript is required for this For Patients Our Science GBM About Us Investors Contact Us Get Updates Notice: JavaScript is required for this Website by Argus   For Patients - SonALASense Get Updates For Patients Our Science GBM About Us Leadership Investors News & Resources Contact We are For Patients We are For Patients We are committed to providing hope in the face of despair with a unique proprietary combination therapy, ALA Sonodynamic Therapy (SDT), for the treatment of recurrent glioblastoma multiforme (rGBM). Patient Centered Approach Aminolevulinic acid (ALA) sonodynamic therapy (SDT) is created through the union of two technologies: ALA tumor targeting and focused ultrasound (FUS) ALA SDT uses an focused ultrasound (MRGFUS) device together with a drug, aminolevulinic acid (ALA), to provide a therapeutic We have compelling data from three independent groups (including SonALAsense’s founding CEO CMO, Stuart Marcus) in three animal brain tumor models demonstrating 70% brain tumor regression and significant extension of survival without damage to surrounding normal brain Both ALA and the MRGFUS device have been shown to be safe and in the brain as they are individually for other indications, allowing SonALAsense to begin a Phase 0 2 clinical trial in rGBM with no additional animal brain tumor model studies Our goal is to turn glioblastoma multiforme (GBM) from a deadly cancer into a manageable disease, turning GBM patients into cancer Metabolic Targeting of GBM GBM cells have a unique metabolic signature different from normal brain cells, causing them to absorb large quantities of the drug aminolevulinic acid (ALA) and to convert it to a fluorescent molecule called protoporphyrin which neurosurgeons use as a visual aid to help them remove the GBM during surgery: Blue Light image — GBM glowing pink Courtesy of Nader Sanai, Ivy Brain Tumor Center In addition to creating fluorescence, protoporphyrin can be “activated” by high energies of light in a process called ALA photodynamic therapy (PDT), which activates oxygen molecules in the cell and causes cell While ALA PDT is and used as topical therapy every day by dermatologists for skin (actinic keratoses), it has also been used experimentally to treat However, the process for treating GBM with ALA PDT is invasive and difficult to Fortunately, we and others have found that focused ultrasound (MRGFUS) can activate essentially the same process as ALA PDT and have developed it in animal models for that purpose the process using MRGFUS instead of light to activate protoporphyrin is called sonodynamic therapy (SDT). MRGFUS is for the noninvasive treatment of essential tremors as well as those arising from Parkinson’s We have partnered with Insightec, the company that developed this tremor therapy, to use a similar device to activate ALA SDT in Learn more about “incisionless surgery” using sound waves to treat instead of a scalpel Image courtesy of Insightec Proposed sonodynamic therapy outpatient procedure for recurrent glioblastoma (rGBM) Step Patient with rGBM receives an intravenous injection of SonALAsense’s proprietary formulation of Step After a few hours during which protoporphyrin accumulates within the rGBM cells, the patient’s head is placed within a helmet inside an MRI machine for FUS Images courtesy of Insightec The entire process is expected to take only a few The system is used to focus ultrasound waves from the approximately ultrasound generating transducers in the helmet over the entire tumor volume, creating light through a process called sonoluminescence and activating the sonodynamic effect in a completely noninvasive The entire process is expected to take only a few We are hopeful that treatment effects on the rGBM tissue will be observed in less than one week, with no significant systemic side effects First Clinical Trial Site Image courtesy of Ivy Brain Tumor Center SonALAsense is proud to announce that we are collaborating with the Ivy Brain Tumor Center at the Barrow Neurological Institute in Phoenix, Nader Sanai, MD, Director, pictured above, has agreed to carry out the first clinical trial of our ALA SDT in the United The Ben and Catherine Ivy Foundation, through a grant to the Ivy Brain Tumor Center, will be funding the entire clinical costs of our Ivy Foundation Ivy Brain Tumor Center For Patients Our Science GBM About Us Investors Contact Us Get Updates Notice: JavaScript is required for this Website by Argus   GBM - Patient Square Capital Announces the Formation of Enavate Sciences to Invest in and Support Therapeutic Companies | Enavate Sciences Home Team Partner Companies News Contact News May 2, Patient Square Capital Announces the Formation of Enavate Sciences to Invest in and Support Therapeutic Companies James Boylan, Accomplished Health Care Executive, Joins Enavate as CEO $300 Million Initial Investment Commitment Received MENLO PARK, , May 2, – Patient Square Capital (“Patient Square”), a leading dedicated health care investment firm, today announced the formation of a new portfolio company, Enavate Sciences , to invest in and enable the growth of therapeutic and enabling technology Enavate has received an initial capital commitment of $300 million from Patient Square and anticipates significant additional funding to be raised over Enavate Sciences will provide capital and strategic growth support to innovative companies to advance and accelerate the development of novel therapies with the intent to improve patients’ health and quality of “Patient Square Capital’s approach to investing in therapeutics focuses primarily on backing talented teams in interesting areas of medicine and progressing multiple clinical programs toward regulatory There are many promising companies with innovative science, however, that do not fit this model,” said Jim Momtazee, Managing Partner of Patient Square and Chairman of the Board of Directors of Enavate “This new platform will support a series of these companies that collectively have similar transformative potential by providing the funds and strategic capabilities necessary to advance therapeutic pipelines, which is particularly important given the scarcity of funding in today’s ” Enavate Sciences will be led by James Boylan, an accomplished health care executive, entrepreneur and innovator with nearly three decades of Boylan most recently served as President and Head of Investment Banking of SVB Leerink, where he architected and led the transformation of Leerink Swann into an health care investment bank that was acquired by SVB Financial in Across his years at SVB Leerink and prior years as a Managing Director at Merrill Lynch, Boylan has worked with hundreds of life sciences and biotechnology companies to develop strategy and complete transactions in capital markets and mergers & Boylan has a broad network of CEO, CFO, board member, venture capital, investor and advisor relationships in the health care He brings to Enavate both his wealth of experience in the life sciences sector as well as his skillset in partnering with entrepreneurs to build companies for At Enavate Sciences, Boylan will assemble a select team of professionals to support Enavate’s various companies in key functions of “company building” in the life sciences sector, including augmenting specific aspects of drug discovery and development, assisting with clinical and market assessments, and providing comprehensive business development “We are in the golden age of therapeutics, where the science has never been better understood and the tools to target disease, engineer therapies and deliver drugs to patients with precision have never been more Yet current financial market dynamics have created significant challenges for therapeutic companies to raise the necessary capital to advance their Therefore, we believe this is an excellent time to bring forward a new platform focused on supporting the continued growth needs of these leading companies,” said James Boylan, Chief Executive Officer of Enavate “I am proud to join the team at Enavate and look forward to announcing our initial investments very soon and helping our partner companies reach their full ” About Enavate Sciences Enavate Sciences is a platform dedicated to supporting therapeutic companies advancing medicines and enabling technologies with transformative potential to address patient Through the application of capital support and operational experience, Enavate strives to enable and empower a diverse portfolio of therapeutics companies to accelerate To learn more about Enavate, please visit . About Patient Square Capital Patient Square Capital is a dedicated health care investment firm that partners with management teams whose products, services and technologies improve We utilize our deep industry expertise, our broad network of relationships and a true partnership approach to make investments in companies that will grow and We believe in the power these companies have to improve patient lives, strengthen communities and create a healthier Patient Square is purpose built by a team of executives, differentiated by the depth of our focus in health care, the breadth of our health care investing experience, and the network we can activate to drive differentiated Most importantly, patients are squarely at the center of all that we For more information, visit . open education resources (which are sourced by ChalkTalk).
